12. CONFIGURABLE EDITOR SYSTEM
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

First launch creates config.json:

    {
      "edit": "micro",
      "view": "micro",
      "info": "Available: micro, nvim, vim, hx, helix, emacs -nw, nano"
    }

External editor selection:
- edit: editor for writing notes
- view: editor for viewing (read-only mode)

Implementation:

    editor_cmd = self.view_editor if read_only else self.edit_editor
    subprocess.run(f"{editor_cmd} {temp_path}", shell=True)

Special handling for nvim autosave commands.
User can change editors without modifying application code.
All terminal editors supported; GUI editors excluded by design.

