15. CONTAINERIZATION & MULTI-USER ARCHITECTURE
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Docker container provides:
- Isolated environment with all dependencies
- SSH access for remote use (port 2222)
- Persistent data volume (/data)
- Symlink: /app/source/notebooks_root → /data/notebooks_root

Multi-user capability emerges from filesystem separation:

    /data/
    ├── user1/
    │   └── notebooks_root/
    ├── user2/
    │   └── notebooks_root/
    └── user3/
        └── notebooks_root/

Each user connects via SSH with their own credentials.
Each user has their own notebook directory.
The same application code serves all users.
UUIDs ensure no cross-user contamination.

Deployment: docker run -d -p 2222:22 -v ./data:/data terminal-notes

