16. GIT-FILTER-REPO AS PYTHON MODULE
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

git-filter-repo is a Python script, not a proper module.
This invention loads it dynamically using importlib:

    filter_repo_path = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), "git_filter_repo.py")
    spec = importlib.util.spec_from_file_location("git_filter_repo", filter_repo_path)
    git_filter_repo = importlib.util.module_from_spec(spec)
    spec.loader.exec_module(git_filter_repo)

This enables:
- Programmatic history rewriting
- Integration into application flow
- Error handling via Python exceptions
- No subprocess calls to external tools
- Bundling with application (no separate installation)

FILTER_REPO_AVAILABLE flag enables graceful fallback.
Hard delete works when available; otherwise suggests installation.

